webpackJsonp([0x5caf15a1fc6e],{644:function(e,a){e.exports={pathContext:{docHtml:'<p align="center">\n  <img src="https://github.com/argoproj/argo-events/blob/ebdbdd4a2a8ce47a0fc6e9a6a63531be2c26148a/docs/assets/k8s.png?raw=true" alt="K8s">\n</p>\n<br/>\n<h1>Resource</h1>\n<p>Resource gateway listens to updates on <strong>any</strong> Kubernetes resource.</p>\n<p>You consider using resource gateway as the watchdog in your cluster, basically monitoring various updated to\ninstalled kubernetes resources. </p>\n<h2>How to define an event source in confimap?</h2>\n<p>An entry in the gateway configmap corresponds to <a href="https://github.com/argoproj/argo-events/blob/ebdbdd4a2a8ce47a0fc6e9a6a63531be2c26148a/gateways/core/resource/config.go#L36-L46">this</a>.</p>\n<h3>Example</h3>\n<p>The <a href="../../../examples/gateways/resource-gateway-configmap.yaml">gateway configmap</a> contains a couple of event sources. </p>\n<p>The <code>workflow-success</code> event source defines configuration to listen to notifications for newly created <code>Argo Workflows</code> and filter these\nworkflows on labels. </p>\n<p>The <code>namespace</code> event source defines configuration to listen to any updates to namespace.</p>\n<h3>Event Payload Structure</h3>\n<p>Kubernetes Object the gateway is watching.</p>\n<h2>Setup</h2>\n<p><strong>1. Install <a href="../../../examples/gateways/resource-gateway-configmap.yaml">Gateway Configmap</a></strong></p>\n<p><strong>2. Install <a href="../../../examples/gateways/resource.yaml">Gateway</a></strong></p>\n<p>Make sure the gateway pod is created.</p>\n<p><strong>3. Install <a href="../../../examples/sensors/resource.yaml">Sensor</a></strong></p>\n<p>Make sure the sensor pod is created.</p>\n<p><strong>4. Trigger workflow</strong></p>\n<p>Create an argo workflow with name <code>my-workflow</code>. As soon as <code>my-workflow</code> succeeds, a new workflow will be triggered.</p>',docPath:"argo-events/gateways/core/resource/readme",proj:"argo-events"}}}});
